    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="537"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d537fn1">The message originated in Canada
                            but was transmitted to Washington via London. It was forwarded by the
                            White House Map Room to Roosevelt, who was then at Hyde Park, in
                            telegram No. <gloss target="#t_White1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                            </gloss> 130, August 26, 1943.</note>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-26">26 August
                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>414. <gloss target="#t_CW1">Colonel Warden</gloss> to President Roosevelt
                    personal and most secret most immediate.</p>
                <p>Should like to arrive Washington Wednesday 1st in time for dinner instead of
                    Monday 30th. Hope this will not be inconvenient to you. I feel I require a
                    little more rest. Will this be all right.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
